OL,3,CFirefighter honoured with Elizabeth
OL,4,CEmblem 28 years after her death
OL,6,F"This will be a sad but proud day for
OL,7,Fall the loved ones whom these heroes
OL,8,Fleft behind, and we offer our
OL,9,Fgratitude to them too for the strength
OL,10,Fand dignity that they have shown, and
OL,11,Fthe immense sacrifice that their
OL,12,Ffamilies have made. We also thank all
OL,13,Fthose who have campaigned for this
OL,14,FEmblem over many years to ensure that
OL,15,Fthe courage of those who keep us safe
OL,16,Fis recognised."
OL,18,FThe design of the Emblem incorporates
OL,19,Fa rosemary wreath, a traditional
OL,20,Fsymbol of remembrance, which surrounds
OL,21,Fthe Tudor Crown.
